<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 13 at 5:37PM EDT  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Van Buren, Allegan,
Barry and Kalamazoo Counties through 700 PM EDT...
At 537 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms near
Bangor, or 9 miles east of South Haven, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Kalamazoo...           Portage...             Holland...
Hastings...            Allegan...             South Haven...
Paw Paw...             Wayland...             Otsego...
Plainwell...           Middleville...         Vicksburg...
Hartford...            Galesburg...           Mattawan...
Lawton...              Bangor...              Decatur...
Nashville...           Schoolcraft...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
